{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Please place categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata (see [[Wikipedia:Wikidata]]) -->

This template is an alternative to {{Tl|Citation needed}}, for the cases where a reference is alluded to, or given in part, but not specified in enough detail. The factuality may or may not be in question.

== Usage ==

{{Tlx|Full citation needed|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}

* Jane Doe refers readers of her book to her journal article covering the experimental methodology.{{Tlx|Full|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}
*: '''Result:''' Jane Doe refers readers of her book to her journal article covering the experimental methodology.{{Full}}
*This template places the article into [[:Category:Articles needing more detailed references]] or a dated subcategory thereof.

This [[Wikipedia:Template|template]] is a [[Wikipedia:Avoid self-references|self-reference]] and so is part of the Wikipedia project rather than the encyclopædic content.

== Redirects ==
* {{Tl|fcn}}
* {{Tl|full}}
* {{Tl|Incomplete citation}}
* {{Tl|Vague citation}}

== See also ==
* {{Tl|Ref expand}}, banner template for when an article needs more than one citation to be completed
* {{Tl|Citation needed}}, for when no source is indicated at all
* {{Tl|Ref improve}}, banner template for when an article needs more than one citation to be added
* [[Wikipedia:Citing sources]], especially [[Wikipedia:Citing sources#Unsourced material|Unsourced material]]
* [[Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources]]
* [[Wikipedia:Template messages/Cleanup/Verifiability and sources]]
* [[Wikipedia:Template messages/Sources of articles]]
* [[Wikipedia:Verifiability]]
* [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Fact and Reference Check]]

