[[Category:Inline citation and verifiability dispute templates]]

}}</includeonly>

{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Please place categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata (see [[Wikipedia:Wikidata]]) -->
{{High-use}}

This template is an alternative to {{Tl|Citation needed}}, for the cases where a reference is alluded to, or given in part, but not specified in enough detail. The factuality may or may not be in question; this template is just about the completeness of the citation. 

For an article with numerous partial citations, consider instead the banner template {{tlx|Full citations needed}}.

== Usage ==

{{Tlx|Full citation needed|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}

The template should be placed outside <code><nowiki><ref>...</ref></nowiki></code> tags.
* <code><nowiki>Nixon resigned August 9, 1974.<ref>''The New York Times''</ref>{{Full citation needed|date=</nowiki>{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}</code>
*: '''Result:''' Nixon resigned August 9, 1974.<ref>''The New York Times''</ref>{{Full citation needed|date={{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}
{{reflist-talk}}

This template places the article into [[:Category:Articles needing more detailed references]] or a dated subcategory thereof.

This [[Wikipedia:Template|template]] is a [[Wikipedia:Avoid self-references|self-reference]] and so is part of the Wikipedia project rather than the encyclopædic content.

== Template data ==

{{TemplateDataHeader}}
<templatedata>
{
	"description": "This inline template is used where a reference is alluded to, or given in part, but not specified in enough detail to identify it.",
	"params": {
		"date": {
			"label": "Month and year",
			"description": "Provides the month and year; e.g., 'January 2013', but not 'jan13'",
			"type": "string",
			"autovalue": "{{subst:CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{subst:CURRENTYEAR}}",
			"suggested": true
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>

== Redirects ==
* {{Tl|}}
* {{Tl|full}}
* {{Tl|Citation broken}}
* {{Tl|Incomplete citation}}
* {{Tl|Vague citation}}

== See also ==
* {{Tlx|Ref expand}} – banner version of this template, for when an article needs many citations to be completed
* {{tlx|Incomplete short citation}} – variant of this inline template for when a short citation is too incomplete to identify which long citation it references
* {{Tlx|Citation needed}} – for when no source is indicated at all
* {{Tlx|Ref improve}} – banner template for when an article needs more than one citation to be added
* {{tlx|Author missing}} – inline template for a specific issue
* {{tlx|Year missing}} – inline template for a specific issue
* {{tlx|Page missing}} – inline template for a specific issue
